info.description:
REST API for collaborative 2D sketch editing.

The Go backend is the authoritative application layer:
- validates Keycloak JWT tokens;
- checks workspace permissions;
- persists sketches, operation log, snapshots and locks;
- invokes the C++ geometric constraint solver;
- broadcasts collaboration events via WebSocket.

WebSocket endpoint is documented as an HTTP upgrade endpoint and uses the message schemas
from the `RealtimeMessage` union.

This document also includes the 3D part-modeling read API merged from docs/swagger_3d.json. 3D state-changing commands remain outside this REST read-side contract.

put.description:
Access rules:
- admin can grant or update reader/editor permissions;
- admin can revoke reader/editor permissions;
- only the sketch creator can grant or revoke admin permissions;
- the creator admin grant cannot be removed from the creator.
